                      "exit_status": "0",
                      "stdout": "21:# Enables integration between zsh and ghostty.\n26:# ghostty-integration won't automatically run. Zsh users who want integration with\n29:#   if [[ -n $GHOSTTY_RESOURCES_DIR ]]; then\n30:#     source \"$GHOSTTY_RESOURCES_DIR\"/shell-integration/zsh/ghostty-integration\n44:    (( ! $+_ghostty_state ))          || builtin return 0  # already initialized\n49:        builtin echo \"Zsh ${ZSH_VERSION} is too old for ghostty shell integration (5.1+ required)\" >&2\n56:    builtin typeset -gi _ghostty_state\n61:    # - It's tempting to do `[[ -t 1 ]] && exec {_ghostty_state}>&1` but we cannot do this\n70:    # - `zmodload zsh/system` and `sysopen -o cloexec -wu _ghostty_fd -- /dev/tty` can\n74:    # - We must open the file descriptor right here rather than in _ghostty_deferred_init\n===\n",
                      "stderr": ""
                    }
